history.content: I'd suggest you to take 189. Given the industry's push towards the ML field, it sure could turn out to be useful knowledge down the road. And with Shewchuck, its not that math-heavy either.

Hello, Spring 2020 is going to be my last semester and I was hoping to get some advice on classes since Berkeley being Berkeley royally cheated me out of my planned schedule. I was originally planning on taking cs 168, 169, and 170, but 169 got cancelled and 170 is currently locked. I'm managed to get into 168, and I'm trying to figure out what other classes to take. I've taken 161, 162, 186, and 188 and was thinking of trying C100, but it seems redundant to take that after 186, or maybe 152, but I'm really software focused so I have no idea if that would be any use at all for industry. If anyone could advise me of any other classes available for Spring that won't be too intense, that would be great. Thanks.
history.subject: Scheduling advice for my last semester
